name: Leavenworth Bouldering
author: Jason Allemann
embed: <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/15793903?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&badge=0&autopause=0&player_id=0&app_id=137790" width="1280" height="720" frameborder="0" title="Leavenworth Bouldering" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>
description:
We spent just over a week climbing in the Leavenworth, Washington area, most of it bouldering.  Leavenworth is a pretty awesome bouldering destination, with a high percentage of excellent problems.

The town itself is also quite interesting, themed in a Bavarian style.  As we were there towards the end of September, Oktoberfest celebrations were just getting into full swing.

Problems included are:
The Break V2
420 Slab V0
Sunny and Steep V2
The Real Thing V4
The Pocket V4
Drugstore Cowboy V3
